- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the compression rates of Tunstall codes, which are a type of data structure used for lossless data compression. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as f-divergences are commonly used in machine learning for model comparison and evaluation. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper may have implications for analyzing information flow and network dynamics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also less likely but possible as the paper may involve analyzing the computational complexity of the algorithms used in the applications discussed.
